# UI Interactions and Motion

## Context

- Apply when implementing button states, screen transitions, or any animated interactions.
- Motion must feel game-like, snappy, and responsive.
- Never use long, gooey animations.

## Requirements

### Button Press Interaction

- On press: `transform: translate(2px, 2px)` and shadow offset reduces.
- Shadow shifts from `8px 8px 0` to `6px 6px 0` (or `6px 6px 0` to `4px 4px 0`).
- Use CSS `:active` pseudo-class.
- Duration: `100–150ms`, `ease-out` timing.

### Hover State (Desktop)

- Slight raise: `transform: translate(-1px, -1px)`.
- Shadow unchanged (maintains sticker effect).
- Use CSS `:hover` pseudo-class.
- Duration: `150ms`, `ease-out` timing.

### Screen Transitions

- Use subtle slide/fade transitions.
- Duration: `180–240ms`.
- Timing: `ease-out`.
- Optional: slide from right for forward navigation, slide to left for back.

### Progress Bars and Countdowns

- Animate smoothly using CSS `transition: width`.
- Duration: match the actual progress time or `200–300ms` for UI feedback.
- Use `ease-out` or `linear` timing depending on context.

### Animation Constraints

- Never use long animations (>500ms) except for intentional delays.
- Never use gooey, elastic, or bouncy easing functions.
- Keep animations snappy and game-like.
- Disable animations for users with `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Examples

<example>
  Valid button press interaction:
  
  ```css
  .answer-button {
    transition: transform 120ms ease-out, box-shadow 120ms ease-out;
  }
  
  .answer-button:active {
    transform: translate(2px, 2px);
    box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--ink);
  }
  ```
</example>

<example type="invalid">
  Invalid: Long, bouncy animation:
  
  ```css
  .answer-button:active {
    transform: scale(0.95);
    transition: transform 600ms cubic-bezier(0.68, -0.55, 0.265, 1.55);
  }
  ```
</example>

<example>
  Valid hover state:
  
  ```css
  .answer-button:hover {
    transform: translate(-1px, -1px);
    /* Shadow stays the same */
  }
  ```
</example>

<example>
  Valid screen transition:
  
  ```css
  .screen-transition {
    transition: opacity 200ms ease-out, transform 200ms ease-out;
  }
  
  .screen-transition.entering {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(20px);
  }
  
  .screen-transition.entered {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateX(0);
  }
  ```
</example>

<example>
  Valid reduced motion support:
  
  ```css
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .answer-button,
    .screen-transition {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
  ```
</example>